NOTICE
======

This directory contains Elastic Workflow YAML files that were derived from
the open-source Splunk SOAR (Phantom) community playbooks repository:

    Project:  Phantom Community Playbooks
    Source:   https://github.com/phantomcyber/playbooks
    Branch:   8.5
    License:  Apache License, Version 2.0
              https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

The files here are TRANSLATIONS, not copies. The original playbooks are
authored in Python with the `phantom.rules` library and a visual Blockly
graph. The translations in this directory re-implement equivalent logic
flow as declarative Elastic Workflow YAML, a separate DSL with a different
runtime, schema, and execution model.

Modifications from the originals
--------------------------------

- Each playbook was re-expressed as an Elastic Workflow YAML document
  with its own description, step names, and structure.
- Phantom `phantom.act(...)` action calls were mapped onto Elastic step
  types (`http`, vendor connectors, `kibana.*`, `elasticsearch.*`, etc.)
  per the connector mapping table in `scripts/validator/` notes.
- Phantom "custom code" blocks were replaced with Elastic primitives
  (`if`, `foreach`, `data.set`) or `ai.prompt` steps, or marked TODO.
- Vendor-specific assets that have no first-class Elastic connector are
  rendered as `http` steps with a TODO comment.
- Long inline markdown report templates from the originals were
  replaced with brief `console` logging or omitted.
- All descriptions, comments, and tags are restated; no docstrings,
  comments, or report templates were copied verbatim from the source.

